  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency WASH response to the new IDPs in Idleb camps</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This proposal aims to provide WASH humanitarian life-saving assistance for 29008 newly IDPs (6099 men,  6372 women, 8300 boys, and 8237 girls) including 234 people of special needs in 24 newly established camps or camps that have been recently expanded in Idleb Gove, Harim district Dana and Maaret Tmisreen Sub-districts for 6 months.
camps name:
Kernaz	                1119
Mukhtar	                1395
Al-Rahma	          770
Basmet Amal	          801
Ebad Alrahman	  815
Halab Lebiyeh	        1925
Al-Difaa Almadani	1005
Al-Muhtasiboon	  750
Jabal Alzawiya	1700
Kansafra	                5445
Al Qalaa   	        6846
Al Qalamoun	        4116
Al Deyaa1	        2321

Furthermore, this proposal will promote personal and public hygiene and limit diseases spread through insects such as Leishmania, etc. This will be reached through a set of integrated activities that include:
-	Water provision for IDPs with an average of 25 liters/day/person 
-	One-round distribution of hygiene kit that is designed to fulfill HHs needs of hygiene and in pursuance with their culture.
-	Establishing latrine blocks in sites where gaps are considering needs of elderlies, and people with disabilities.
-	Waste management deporting to main dumps that confront to daily health conditions. 
-	Septic tanks desludging and deporting them to main sanitation with ensuring that not making pressure to them. 
Kindly refer to Annex 6 services matrix v2. 
In confront all SPHERE project minimum standards, and AISC committee guidance, Saed will implement all previously proposed WASH activities during the project duration. 
Continuous military hostilities, and larges displacement waves that north rural Idleb lives now, enlarge targeted camps&#x2019; expansion and IDPs numbers increment, for that, Saed will track IDPs arrivals to those camps continuously and inform WASH and SCHF team with any proposed changes that may include: 
1.	Saed to fetch other additional funds to gap the needs. 
2.	Scaling down of intervention duration and fetch for other funds or partners to continue services provision.</narrative>
  </description>
